{
  "text": "In this section we build upon a finding by [CITATION_1] that a Divisia consumption price index is of essential importance when expressing comprehensive NNP in real prices. By using such a price index, we show that a claim made by Dasgupta and Maler (2000, Section 7.1) -namely that comprehensive real NNP cannot be used for intertemporal welfare comparisons -is incorrect.",
